section.p:
As an example, consider a new problem in which we try to solve the
following system of equations,
\begin{aligned}[t]
\begin{cases}
2x+3y \amp = 7\\
5x+4y \amp = 9
\end{cases}
\end{aligned}

figure.caption:
Graphs of three power functions, f(x) = \sqrt{x}
(red, solid),  g(x) = x (black, dashed),  h(x) = x^2
(blue, dotted).

Graphs of two rational functions, f(x) =
\dfrac{x}{1+x} (red, solid) and g(x) = \dfrac{x}{1+x^2}
(black, dashed).

subsection.figure:
One of the simpler versions of an SIR compartment
model.



\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=2.5cm,auto,>=latex]
    \node [draw, minimum size=1cm, fill=blue] (a)
{\textcolor{white}{\(\mathbf S\)}};
    \node [draw, minimum size=1cm, fill=red] (b) [right of=a]
{\textcolor{white}{\(\mathbf I\)}};
    \node [draw, minimum size=1cm, fill=black] (c) [right of=b]
{\textcolor{white}{\(\mathbf R\)}};
    \node (d) [above right of = b] {};
    \path[->, thick] (a) edge node {\small Infection} (b);
    \path[->, thick] (b) edge node {\small Recovery} (c);
    \path[->, thick] (b) edge [] node {\small Death} (d);
    \path[->, bend right, out=90, in=90, thick] (c) edge node {\small
Loss of immunity} (a);
\end{tikzpicture}

